"title": "5720: mothers, examples of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5720",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Examples are given in Scripture of notable mothers, mothers-in-law and grandmothers.</p>\n<h2>Eve, the mother of all the living</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:20\">GEN 3:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16\">GEN 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>Hagar, the mother of Ishmael</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:1-Gen16:4\">GEN 16:1–16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:15\">GEN 16:15</a></p>\n<h2>Sarah, the mother of Isaac</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:1-Gen21:3\">GEN 21:1–21:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:15-Gen17:19\">GEN 17:15–17:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:10-Gen18:14\">GEN 18:10–18:14</a></p>\n<h2>Rebekah, mother of Esau and Jacob</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:21\">GEN 25:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:24\">GEN 25:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:5-Gen27:17\">GEN 27:5–27:17</a></p>\n<h2>Rachel, mother of Joseph and Benjamin</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:22-Gen30:24\">GEN 30:22–30:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:16-Gen35:18\">GEN 35:16–35:18</a></p>\n<h2>Jochebed, mother of Moses</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:1-Exod2:2\">EXO 2:1–2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:20\">EXO 6:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:23\">HEB 11:23</a></p>\n<h2>Naomi, Ruth's mother-in-law</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:15\">RUT 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:13-Ruth4:17\">RUT 4:13–4:17</a></p>\n<h2>Hannah, mother of Samuel</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:2\">1SA 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:11\">1SA 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:20\">1SA 1:20</a></p>\n<h2>Jezebel, who taught her sons to worship Baal rather than the LORD</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:52\">1KI 22:52</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:22\">2KI 9:22</a></p>\n<h2>The Shunammite woman</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:16-2Kgs4:22\">2KI 4:16–4:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:32-2Kgs4:37\">2KI 4:32–4:37</a></p>\n<h2>Elizabeth, mother of John the Baptist</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:5-Luke1:7\">LUK 1:5–1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:13\">LUK 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:24-Luke1:25\">LUK 1:24–1:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:57\">LUK 1:57</a></p>\n<h2>Mary, mother of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:6-Luke2:7\">LUK 2:6–2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:18\">MAT 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:26-Luke1:31\">LUK 1:26–1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:38\">LUK 1:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:19\">LUK 2:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:1-John2:5\">JHN 2:1–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:25-John19:27\">JHN 19:25–19:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:14\">ACT 1:14</a></p>\n<h2>Herodias, a treacherous mother</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:8\">MAT 14:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:24-Mark6:25\">MRK 6:24–6:25</a></p>\n<h2>Rufus' mother, a mother to Paul</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:13\">ROM 16:13</a></p>\n<h2>Lois and Eunice, a godly grandmother and a mother</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:5\">2TI 1:5</a></p>",
